prop_demo_merge_deploy	demo/deployment-v2.md	merge	proposed	medium	0.82	{"diff": {"after": "Unified deployment guide covering both Docker Compose and Kubernetes.", "before": "deployment.md and deployment-v2.md contain duplicate instructions."}, "draft": "# Deployment\\n\\nDeploy using Docker Compose (production) or Kubernetes (cloud).\\n\\n## Docker Compose\\n\\nRun `docker compose -f docker-compose.prod.yml up -d`.\\n\\n## Kubernetes\\n\\nApply manifests with `kubectl apply -f k8s/`.\\n\\n## Rollback\\n\\nDocker: `docker compose down` + redeploy previous image.\\nKubernetes: `kubectl rollout undo deployment/app`.\\n", "action": "merge", "citations": [{"docId": "demo/deployment.md", "score": 0.91}, {"docId": "demo/deployment-v2.md", "score": 0.91}], "confidence": 0.82, "risk_level": "medium", "proposal_id": "prop_demo_merge_deploy", "target_doc_id": "demo/deployment-v2.md", "guardian_reasoning": "Merging the two deployment docs reduces confusion and eliminates the duplicate-of edge."}	2026-06-24 21:35:27.509161+00	2026-06-24 21:36:38.740688+00	\N
prop_demo_fix_stale	demo/deployment.md	update	applied	low	0.94	{"diff": {"after": "Updated with image tagging best practices.", "before": "Deployment doc was stale (last verified at old789)."}, "draft": "# Deployment\\n\\nDeploy using Docker Compose.\\n\\n## Production\\n\\nRun `docker compose -f docker-compose.prod.yml up -d`.\\n\\n## Rollback\\n\\nUse `docker compose down` then redeploy the previous image tag.\\n\\n## Updated 2026-06-24\\n\\nAdded note on image tagging best practices.\\n", "action": "update", "citations": [{"docId": "demo/deployment.md", "score": 0.94}], "confidence": 0.94, "risk_level": "low", "proposal_id": "prop_demo_fix_stale", "target_doc_id": "demo/deployment.md", "guardian_reasoning": "Straightforward content update with low risk."}	2026-06-24 21:35:27.509161+00	2026-06-24 21:36:38.740688+00	2026-06-24 21:36:38.763959+00
prop_demo_resolve_conflict	demo/security-policy.md	deprecate	needs-review	high	0.75	{"diff": {"after": "Legacy policy deprecated with pointer to zero-trust policy.", "before": "Legacy JWT auth policy conflicts with zero-trust policy."}, "draft": "# Security Policy (DEPRECATED)\\n\\n> **Deprecated 2026-07-01.** This policy has been superseded by the [Zero-Trust Security Policy](zero-trust-policy.md).\\n\\nPlease refer to the zero-trust policy for current authentication requirements.\\n", "action": "deprecate", "citations": [{"docId": "demo/security-policy.md", "score": 0.87}, {"docId": "demo/zero-trust-policy.md", "score": 0.87}], "confidence": 0.75, "risk_level": "high", "proposal_id": "prop_demo_resolve_conflict", "target_doc_id": "demo/security-policy.md", "guardian_reasoning": "Deprecating the legacy policy resolves the conflict edge. High risk because it changes auth documentation — staged approval required."}	2026-06-24 21:35:27.509161+00	2026-06-24 21:36:38.740688+00	\N
